Through Flight, To the Stars

Orchestral Intro
→ Verse 1 (current humanity / struggle)
→ Chorus (flight / unity / stars)
→ Verse 2 (engineering / stewardship / civilization)
→ Chorus (larger and stronger)
→ Bridge (quiet reflective section)
→ Final Crescendo Chorus
→ Closing Invocation

Through fields of earth and rising air,
We learned that all who live must share,
No life beneath another stands,
We rise together, hand in hand.

When fear had dimmed the human flame,
And fractured worlds forgot their name,
We chose not conquest, crown, nor war,
But open skies and brighter stars.

From fields of earth and waking sky,
Through forged horizons we arise,
With steady hand and lifted eyes,
We build the road where silence lies.

Per Avia, Ad Astra calls,
Beyond the night that held us small,
Through craft and care, through will and light,
We build tomorrow into flight.

No throne of gold, no tyrant’s claim,
But common voice and common flame,
Through labor joined and knowledge shared,
We shape the future wisely dared.

No child abandoned to the cold,
No mind reduced to bought and sold,
Through knowledge free and labor fair,
We lift each other through the air.

From engines forged and visions drawn,
To silent stations past the dawn,
The Commonwealth shall carry far
A future shaped by every heart.

And when the distant heavens gleam,
Beyond the edge of ancient dreams,
Aevoria still shall carry far,
Through flight, unto the stars.

Through cloud and flame, through night afar,
By craft and will we cross the dark,
Per Avia, Ad Astra calls,
The Ascending Arc beyond us all.

And when at last the heavens sing,
With countless lights awakening,
Aevoria still shall guide afar:
Through flight, unto the stars.


[Orchestral Intro — slow brass, strings, distant choir]

From silent earth and storm-worn years,
We rose beyond division’s fears,
Not bound by throne, nor greed, nor war,
But drawn together toward the stars.

[CHORUS]

Through flight, through light, together we rise,
Beyond the clouds, beyond the skies,
Per Avia, Ad Astra calls,
One future shared among us all.

No life beneath another stands,
We build tomorrow hand in hand,
Through craft and care our voices soar:
Through flight, unto the stars.

[Verse II]

From engines forged and visions drawn,
To stations waiting past the dawn,
We crossed the night through will and flame,
And carried hope where silence reigned.

Through open knowledge freely shared,
Through labor honest, wise, and fair,
The Commonwealth shall carry far
The living light of every heart.

[CHORUS — stronger instrumentation]

Through flight, through light, together we rise,
Beyond the clouds, beyond the skies,
Per Avia, Ad Astra calls,
One future shared among us all.

No child abandoned to the cold,
No mind reduced to bought and sold,
Through courage joined our spirits soar:
Through flight, unto the stars.

[Bridge — quieter, reflective]

And when the distant heavens sing,
With countless lights awakening,
May those who follow still recall
We rose because we rose for all.

[FINAL CHORUS — full orchestral crescendo]

Through flight, through light, together we rise,
Beyond the dark of ancient skies,
Per Avia, Ad Astra calls,
The Ascending Arc shall guide us all.

No life beneath another stands,
We build tomorrow hand in hand,
Aevoria shall carry far:
Through flight… unto the stars.

[Closing orchestral resolve]










